      "id": "PopularPost218563",
      "post_content": "I used 4 of these in my mono red \"choices\" deck for a long time. They fit the \"choice\" theme well, but they're pretty weak, even for casual play. Best case scenario, you do 2 damage per turn starting on turn 5. Now, it's not a great comparison, but [Chandra's Phoenix](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chandra's Phoenix) can start doing 2 damage per turn starting on turn 3 AND can be easily returned from the graveyard when it is inevitably killed.",
